title: Warriors women's tennis comes back to beat Bates
text:
Warriors women's tennis comes back to beat Bates 
After dropping two of the three doubles matches to fall behind early, the Merrimack womenâ€™s tennis team came back to win five of the six singles matches to pull out a 6-3 win over Bates. 
Grace Messina won both of her matches, teaming with Chealsey Giatrelis to win at first doubles 8-1 before also winning at first singles 6-4, 7-5. Mana Seifaei won at third singles 6-2, 6-2; Lauren Persson won at fourth singles 6-2, 4-6, 7-5; Danielle Dunn won at fifth singles 6-4, 6-1 and Celine Mende won at sixth singles 6-2, 6-1 to wrap up the win.
